Key Match Events: Christian Eriksen scored a stunning late winner to give Denmark a 2-1 victory over Sweden.
Eriksen found Pierre-Emile Hojbjerg at the near post for an easy finish in the first minute.
Alexander Isak scored for Sweden seven minutes after Denmark's first goal.
Eriksen's curling, dipping strike in the 86th minute secured the win for Denmark.
Post-Match Reflections: Denmark coach Kasper Hjulmand gave credit to Sweden's coach Jon Dahl Tomasson for his work with the team.
Hjulmand mentioned that Denmark gave away too many turnovers in the first half.
Eriksen expressed happiness for assisting the opening goal and scoring the winner.
Eriksen acknowledged the importance of scoring from a set piece to create calm in the team.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Sweden's Danish coach Jon Dahl Tomasson was inducted into the Danish football Hall Of Fame ahead of kickoff.
